column778:
29/Oct/25 2:53 AM;712020:acbca271-a1bb-4ec4-b675-05befb136032;[~accountid:712020:cee8f402-f274-4476-b4df-0db60444ee7c] 

{noformat}with edw as (
select *
from coursera_warehouse.edw_prod.mailspin_template
)
,
eds as (
  select *
  from dev.silver.courral_mailspin_template_main_vw
)

select eds.template_id, eds.template_name, edw.template_name, eds.template_subject, edw.template_subject, eds.template_description, edw.template_description, eds.template_body, edw.template_body
from edw join eds on edw.template_id = eds.template_id
where edw.template_name <> eds.template_name{noformat}
column779: 29/Oct/25 3:03 AM;712020:cee8f402-f274-4476-b4df-0db60444ee7c;[~accountid:712020:acbca271-a1bb-4ec4-b675-05befb136032] I checked in my use case and I see there are {{836}} such mismatches out of {{16482}} templates. Also, for me these changes will not affect as I am aggregating it to get the email metrics on campaign level. But for this table I would recommend you to take the necessary steps to match EDW and EDS as it would have different other use cases unlike mine
column780:

But template_body differs completely due to some xml structure and the spaces involved in the storage.

20/Nov/25 11:01 PM;712020:9bbf171f-2c84-4976-8af1-657204735bd5;Upon checking the view {{prod.silver.enterprise_user_rosters_vw}} and comparing it with the EDW table {{prod.enterprise_user_rosters}}, there are some differences in the schema of both tables. However, we can ignore them as the underlying table contains all the fields, and we can surface any necessary fields to the view if needed. One notable difference is that we have {{roster_id}} in EDW and {{id}} in EDS, but this can be ignored as all downstream tables use the column correctly to retrieve results. The row count in both tables also matches, although there are a couple of additional records in EDS.

Based on this investigation marking this ticket as done.

column772:
10/Nov/25 2:41 AM;712020:acbca271-a1bb-4ec4-b675-05befb136032;We can see below differences for mentioned columns between EDS and EDW table.
widget_macros for almost 100% of records cause somehow macros weren’t being populated in EDW at all, while we are getting same on EDS end, which is matching with online data as per redash.

For widget_name and widget_security_content_policy we are seeing difference due to different treatment of specials characters like \n, \r, \t. In EDS these characters are getting flattened or taking their actual values and hence causing above difference.

column776:
04/Dec/25 2:51 AM;712020:acbca271-a1bb-4ec4-b675-05befb136032;In the deduplication step, there is no ordering over specific column, Data is only being partitioned over post_id and hence being picked one record randomly. Due to which we may observe difference in course_membership_role, as it’s being picked randomly on EDW end.

On EDS end, we are picking latest course_membership_role to get the latest info on a user for corresponding course_id and user_id.
